strings.Value: "To die in battle is a true honor."
"There is no better death than death in battle."
"Death comes to us all. The real question is how we live â€” with honor, or with shame."
"Once I sought death. No more. Something has changed."
"I confess, I do not understand that sentiment. Death means pain, and separation from loved ones. Why should someone feel good about it?"
"Well, it might be an honor for the dead person. But it still makes me sad!"
"There is nothing good about death. Heroic words cannot heal wounds. They only numb the pain."
